Since 2011, the Greenlandic national broadcaster [[Kalaallit Nunaata Radioa]] (KNR) has attempted to gain EBU membership and thus participate independently in the Eurovision Song Contest. However KNR cannot obtain EBU membership due to the autonomous country not being independent from the [[Kingdom of Denmark]]. [[Greenland]] has broadcast the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2011]] on [[Broadcast delay|tape delay]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=Greenland: Will Not Broadcast Eurovision 2016|url=https://eurovoix.com/2016/05/03/greenland-will-not-broadcast-eurovision-2016/|website=eurovoix.com|publisher=Eurovoix|accessdate=12 September 2016|date=3 May 2016}}</ref> On 4 May 2017, it was announced that Greenland would broadcast the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2017|2017 contest]] final on delay.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eurovoix.com/2017/05/04/greenland-knr-to-broadcast-eurovision-2017-on-timeshift/|title=Greenland: KNR to broadcast Eurovision 2017 on timeshift|date=4 May 2017|website=Eurovoix|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|accessdate=4 May 2017}}</ref>
