'''Vilnius Queer Festival “Kreivės”''' is a cultural and social initiative which started in 2014. It is neither the first nor the only queer festival in the region or [[Lithuania]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cgiii.com/cgiii-events/september/item/vilnius-lgbt-festival|title=Kreives: Vilnius LGBT* Festival  - CGiii...for LGBT films, filmmakers & festivals|last=Editor|first=CGiii|website=cgiii.com|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref> The term "Kreivės" from the Lithuanian language means "the сurves".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.alfa.lt/straipsnis/50296027/sidabrines-gerves-skrydis-kurie-lietuvos-kino-filmai-pretenduoja-gauti-apdovanojimus|title=„Sidabrinės gervės“ skrydis. Kurie Lietuvos kino filmai pretenduoja gauti apdovanojimus?|work=alfa.lt|access-date=2018-06-12|language=lt-LT}}</ref>

The festival is open to feature films, documentaries and short films focusing on Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender, Queer, Intersex themes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://renginiai.kasvyksta.lt/46025/vilniaus-queer-festivalis-kreives|title=Vilniaus queer festivalis „Kreivės“|website=renginiai.kasvyksta.lt|language=lt|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref> Nonetheless, building on earlier and cooperating with current other [[queer]] initiatives, the festival aspires to be a unique space for film screenings, events and community building.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kinfo.lt/prasideda-treciasis-vilniaus-lgbt-festivalis-kreives/|title=Prasideda trečiasis Vilniaus LGBT* festivalis "Kreivės" {{!}} KINFO.LT|website=kinfo.lt|language=lt-LT|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref> Working languages of the festival are Lithuanian and English.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.15min.lt/kultura/naujiena/renginiai/vilniaus-lgbt-festivalis-kreives-jau-po-dvieju-savaiciu-29-445019|title=Vilniaus LGBT festivalis „Kreivės“ – jau po dviejų savaičių|work=15min.lt|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref> Works accepted to screen at the festival are categorised in competitive and non-competitive categories at the  discretion of "Kreivės".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://manoteises.lt/straipsnis/festivalis-kurio-demesio-centre-lgbt-patirtys/|title=Festivalis, kurio dėmesio centre – LGBT* patirtys - Mano teisės|website=manoteises.lt|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref> 

Held in a little cinema in central [[Vilnius]] and venues across the town, "Kreivės" events attract several thousand visitors each year.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lgl.lt/naujienos/birzeli-vyksiantis-festivalis-kreives-pristato-filmu-programa/|title=Birželį vyksiantis festivalis „Kreivės“ pristato filmų programą - LGL|date=2016-06-01|work=LGL|access-date=2018-06-12|language=lt-LT}}</ref> Entrance to the festival's film screenings and events is donation-based.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://filmfreeway.com/Kreives|title=Vilnius queer festival "Kreivės"|website=FilmFreeway|language=en|access-date=2018-06-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://370.diena.lt/2017/09/10/festivalis-kurio-demesio-centre-lgbt-patirtys/|title=Festivalis , kurio dėmesio centre – „ LGBT“* patirtys|work=370|access-date=2018-06-12|language=lt-LT}}</ref>

The festival is organised by “In Corpore<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://in-co.lt/|title=In Corpore|website=in-co.lt|access-date=2018-06-12}}</ref>” in cooperation with other organisations and individual activists and artists. <ref>http://festivaliskreives.lt/en/</ref>

==2017 winners and featured movies==
* Best Short Film: ''Beautiful figure (Szép alak)'': A realistic tale of unrequited desire and infatuation.<ref>{{Citation|last=Kis|first=Hajni|title=Szép alak|date=2016-09|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5266674/|others=Brigitta Egyed, Hanna Milovits, Mari Nagy|accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>
